I can't go back because I'm worried about Makoto!

I thought I saw Makoto enter this building, but suddenly I
got scared of being caught for trespassing by the man with
sunglasses, and without really searching, I fled from the
building.

Honestly, I've never heard of a dojo being around here, but
I convinced myself it must be something new. Still, I became
worried afterwards and couldn't sleep well that night.

The next day. I had a terrible headache from lack of sleep,
but I decided to go to school. I must have been mistaken
yesterday. Today I should be able to go to school with
Makoto. With that thought, I opened the front door, but
Makoto was nowhere to be seen outside my house.
(Makoto might be here! I can't just escape from this place!)

"With a building this big, it's no surprise there's an
elevator. But if I ride it, they'll know I've broken in, so
I'll use the stairs."

"There's a phone. But it seems to be for indoor use only."

"Fire extinguishers and fire alarms, huh. There are
sprinklers on the ceiling too, seems like they're fully
prepared for fires."

(I'm curious if that guy with the sunglasses is still
around. Maybe I should check, just to be sure?)
